com.sap.conn.jco.ext.DataProviderException

  • Packages that use DataProviderException 
    Package Description
    com.sap.conn.jco.ext
    Provides all interfaces that are offered for embedding JCo into an application server environment.

    • Uses of DataProviderException in com.sap.conn.jco.ext

      Methods in com.sap.conn.jco.ext that throw DataProviderException 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      default X509Certificate DestinationDataProvider.getClientCertificate(String destinationName)
      This method is invoked by the JCo runtime if JCO_TLS_CLIENT_CERTIFICATE_LOGON is set in order to get the client certificate which will be used in the user logon at the backend when WebSocket communication is established.
      Properties DestinationDataProvider.getDestinationProperties(String destinationName)
      This method shall return a properties object that contains a subset of the supported properties mentioned above which represent the configuration of the given destination in your destination configuration repository.
      Properties ServerDataProvider.getServerProperties(String serverName)
      This method shall return a properties object that contains a subset of the supported properties mentioned above which represent the configuration of the given JCoServer in your server configuration repository.
      default SSLContext DestinationDataProvider.getSSLContext(String destinationName)
      This method is invoked by the JCo runtime in order to get a SSLContext which is then used to establish a secure connection in case that a WebSocket communication shall be established.
      default SSLContext ServerDataProvider.getSSLServerContext(String serverName)
      This method is invoked by the JCo runtime in order to get a SSLContext which is then used to establish a secure connection in case that a WebSocket server shall be established.
